description.narrative: 105 COVID-19 Increased capacity of IPs to manage outbreak and vaccination campaign & provision of supplies, which contributes to Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care (Covid), Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions (Covid). title.narrative: 105 COVID-19 Increased capacity of IPs to manage outbreak and vaccination campaign & provision of supplies

description.narrative: UNICEF in India continued to work alongside MoHFW and state governments in close coordination with WHO, to support risk communication for the disease prevention, containment measures, screening, testing, tracing and referral of patients, and enhanced care for COVID-19 cases through the procurement of oxygen products, screening and testing equipment, capacity strengthening of and protection of health care providers and psychosocial support to them. UNICEF has also played a critical role in the preparedness to the introduction and roll out of COVID-19 vaccines in India including procurement of cold chain equipment and other consumables. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:05/01/2022
